# What Does "missing separator" Mean?

This is the most common Makefile error.

The issue is almost always:

> Using spaces instead of a real TAB character.

Makefiles are extremely strict.

Every command under a target MUST begin with a real tab.

---

# WRONG Example (Spaces)

```makefile
setup:
    python3 -m venv mlops-venv
```

The indentation above uses spaces.

Make will fail.

---

# CORRECT Example (TAB)

```makefile
setup:
	python3 -m venv mlops-venv
```

The line begins with a real tab character.

---

# Step 4 — Open the Makefile

Open:

```bash
Makefile
```

Delete everything currently inside it.

Replace it with the following:

---

# Correct Makefile

```makefile
.PHONY: setup data train test clean all

all: setup data train test

setup:
	python3 -m venv mlops-venv
	mlops-venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt

data:
	python src/data/process_data.py

train:
	python src/models/train.py

test:
	pytest tests/

clean:
	find . -type d -name "__pycache__" -exec rm -rf {} +
	rm -rf .pytest_cache
	rm -rf models/*
```

---

# IMPORTANT WARNING

Every command line must begin with a REAL TAB.

Not spaces.

